    front: "In Glosten-Milgrom (1985), what does the bid-ask spread equal under a risk-neutral competitive market maker?",
    back: "The pure adverse-selection cost — the difference between the conditional expected value given a buy and given a sell. With zero inventory or order-processing costs, the spread is entirely informational.",
