    back: "a = E[V | buy] — the expected fundamental value given that the incoming order is a buy. Bayes' rule weights the two value states by the PRIOR on V (θ₀, 1−θ₀), not by the informed fraction μ; μ enters through the state-conditional order probabilities P(buy | V).",
    latex: "a = \\mathbb{E}[V \\mid \\text{buy}] = \\frac{\\theta_0 P(\\text{buy} \\mid V=\\bar{V}) \\bar{V} + (1-\\theta_0) P(\\text{buy} \\mid V=\\underline{V}) \\underline{V}}{\\theta_0 P(\\text{buy} \\mid V=\\bar{V}) + (1-\\theta_0) P(\\text{buy} \\mid V=\\underline{V})}",
