    front: "What is the structural difference between sequential-trade and batch-trade models?",
    back: "Sequential-trade (Glosten-Milgrom) processes one order at a time and updates quotes continuously. Batch-trade (Kyle) aggregates orders within a window and clears them at a single price set by a competitive auctioneer.",
