    back: "Monotonically increasing in μ. As the informed fraction grows, each trade is more likely informational, raising adverse-selection risk and widening the spread. As μ → 1 the ask → V̄ and the bid → V_low, so the spread approaches its maximum (V̄ − V_low) and the market effectively breaks down — liquidity evaporates as the MM can no longer quote profitably inside the value range.",
